Onward to November—let's elect the first Latina ever to hold the position of Mayor of Tucson!
I send my deep appreciation to all of the primary candidates—it takes strong commitment and vision for one’s community to seek public service.

You know your city is rich with community leaders when you have competitive primaries with formidable candidates. While there is still a general election to win in November I am confident that Tucson will vote for the strong leaders elected last night.

With joy I send a huge congratulations to @TucsonRomero @PaulTucson @NikkiLeeAZ and Lane Santa Cruz for their successful campaigns. I look forward to working together to enhance and deliver for the great city we call home.
